name: PixelFem #59  - Maria Orosa
description:
Have you ever had banana ketchup? It’s made of mashed banana, sugar, vinegar and spices, mixed with a bit of red food colouring to make it look like ‘normal’ ketchup. It was first produced in the Philippines during World War II, due to a lack of tomatoes and tons of bananas! It sounds like a strange combination, but the person behind it is fantastic - Maria Orosa.

✺This work is part of PixelFems, an evolving project on the Tezos blockchain celebrating iconic women from the past and present✺
